ZCZC EE14
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 162300 UTC
ON FRIDAY EVENING A LARGE RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE 1047 WILL BE CENTRED
NEAR GERMAN BIGHT WITH AN ATLANTIC LOW 997 CENTRED TO THE SW OF ICELAND.
DURING FRIDAY AND SATURDAY THE HIGH WILL SLWY BUILD AND MOV NEWARDS TO BE
CENTRED OVER SKAGGERAK 1050 BY MIDDAY SATURDAY. THEN DECLINING TO 1038
BY MONDAY EVENING AT WHICH TIME IT IS EXP TO BE CENTRED OVER THE BALTIC SEA.
MEANWHILE THE ATLANTIC LOW WILL FILL AS IT TRACKS STEADILY NEWARDS PASSING
CLOSE TO THE S COAST OF ICELAND ON SATURDAY THEN MOV AWAY. HIGH PRESSURE
WILL FOLLOW THE SAME TRACK DURING SUNDAY REACHING NORWAY SUNDAY NIGHT MERGING
WITH THE HIGH OVER THE BALTIC SEA. GALE OR NEAR GALE SE WINDS MAY AFFECT
THE NWERN PART OF FITZROY SOLE AND SHANNON ON FRIDAY EVENING WITH WINDS
SLWY EASING INTO SATURDAY. NO HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP IN NITON ON SUNDAY
OR MONDAY
